<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1323,398,1879]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,464,724,750]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Description.</emphasis>
Size up to 1.0 mm. Colour dark, blue-violet with numerous paler spots, ventral side and extremities paler. Cuticle with fine primary granulation. Ocelli 8+8, G and H slightly smaller. PAO narrow elliptical, not constricted, 0.9–1.2 as long as U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1184,1192,820,834]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">3</subScript>
. Maxillary outer lobe with 4 sublobal hairs and bifurcate palp. Maxillary head with short unmodified lamellae (
<figureCitation box="[384,477,887,913]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="9.[264,382,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[303,1277,313,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-128@9.[277,1313,308,1403]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Maxillary head in Proisotoma minuta (18), Ballistura schoetti (19), Strenzketoma buddenbrocki (20), Scutisotoma karadagi sp.n. (21), Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. (22), and “Proisotoma” ripicola (23) (1–6 maxillary lamellae)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071472/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Labral formula 4/554. Labium with a complete set of papillae and guards (
<figureCitation box="[360,449,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–17" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1171,1195]" captionTargetBox="[279,1279,325,1140]" captionTargetId="figure-234@8.[264,1322,312,1147]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12–17. Morphological characters of the Proisotoma-complex. 12–14, inner side of Ti. 2 in Proisotoma minuta (12) and Ballistura schoetti (13–14) (tibiotarsal chaetae B4, B5, and B4/5); 15–17, labial palp in Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. (15), P. clavipila (16), and S. tianshanica (17) (papilla E, and guard e7 encircled)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071470/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Proximal chaetae 3, basomedian chaetae 4. Ventral side of a head with 4–5+4–5 postlabial chaetae. Ant.1 with 2 basal microsensilla (bms) in dorsal and ventral position, and 2 ventral sensilla (s). Ant.2 with 3 bms and one laterodistal s, Ant.3 with one bms and 6 distal s (
<quantity box="[495,543,1047,1073]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
AO and two lateral of similar length) (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1098,1047,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–71" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-246@28.[297,1305,462,1343]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 67–71. Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. 67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Lateral guards of AO slightly longer than the inner pair of sensilla. Additional sensilla on Ant.2–3 present in males. Sensilla on Ant.4 hardly differentiated, subapical organite small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1323,398,1879]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Dorsal axial chaetom of Th.II–Abd.III as 8–9,7–8/5,5,5–6. Thorax without ventral axial chaetae. Macrochaetae differentiated laterally on Th.II–III and on tip of abdomen, medial ones on Abd.V are 0.3–0.4 as long as tergite. Sensilla on tergites short and slightly thickened. Sensillary formula 33/22224 (s) and 11/111 (ms). Sensilla on Abd.I–III in almost mid-tergite position (medial sensillum on Abd.III set in posterior 1/3 of the tergite). On Abd.V the two medial and two lateral sensilla set far apart (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1108,1367,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–71" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-246@28.[297,1305,462,1343]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 67–71. Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. 67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). The most lateral sensillum (accp4) displaced anteriorly, usually set in front of sensillum accp3. In the 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1322,1407,1433]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
population the microsensillum of Abd.III set rather far from the lateral sensillum, more medially (unlike 
<figureCitation box="[464,606,1487,1513]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="30.[264,382,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[310,1260,721,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-221@30.[286,1294,702,1558]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Scutisotoma longisensilla sp.n. 72, posterior side of manubrium; 73, 74, posterior and anterior sides of dens; 75, Ant.3, lateral view (ls – lateral sensilla); 76–78, variants in position of sensillum and microsensillum on Abd.III (p-chaetae connected by a line, s: sensillum, ms: microsensillum); 79, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071492/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs. 76–78</figureCitation>
, see also remarks below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1323,398,1879]" lastBlockId="28.[264,1323,284,430]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Unguis rather slender, without inner tooth. The number of chaetae on Ti.1–3 is 21-21- 26(27), like the basic set. B-row on Ti.1-2 with 7 chaetae. Chaetae x and B 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1184,1192,1583,1597]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">5</subScript>
on Ti. 
<quantity box="[1273,1323,1567,1593]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
subadult males slightly differentiated (full–sized males not seen). Tibiotarsal tenent chaetae (1-2-2) on Ti.1–3 clearly clavate, shorter than unguis (0.6–0.8 as long as U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1297,1305,1667,1681]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">3</subScript>
). Ventral tube with 4+4 laterodistal and 5–6 posterior chaetae. Tenaculum with 4+4 teeth and one chaeta. Anterior furcal subcoxa with 13–16, posterior with 9–10 chaetae. Anterior surface of manubrium with a pair of distal chaetae. Posterior surface with 17–20+17–20 chaetae on the main part and 4–5 on each laterobasal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[974,1063,1813,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–71" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-246@28.[297,1305,462,1343]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 67–71. Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. 67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Dens with 8–11(12) anterior chaetae, usually arranged as 3,2,1,1...1 (basal quarter to one third of dens (usually about 1/4) without chaetae, 
<figureCitation box="[592,735,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–71" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-246@28.[297,1305,462,1343]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 67–71. Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. 67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs. 67, 69</figureCitation>
). Posterior side of dens crenulated, usually with 8 chaetae (4 basal, 1 outer, 2 inner and 1 subapical near mucro, 
<figureCitation box="[1038,1129,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–71" captionStartId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-246@28.[297,1305,462,1343]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 67–71. Scutisotoma kolymica sp.n. 67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Mucro with 3 subequal teeth which set close together. Ratio of manubrium: dens: mucro = 4.9–6.5: 4.0–5.1: 1. Each anal lobe with 3 tiny chaetae of similar length.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071490" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5071490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071490/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" startId="28.[264,382,1347,1371]" targetBox="[313,1257,478,1328]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1323,1347,1440]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,466,1347,1371]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">FIGURES 67–71.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[476,712,1348,1371]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[476,712,1348,1371]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Scutisotoma kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,775,1347,1371]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[722,775,1347,1371]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
67–68, anterior and posterior views of furca; 69, dens laterally; 70, Ant.3, lateral view (ls: lateral sensilla); 71, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1323,1491,1878]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,605,1491,1517]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Intraspecific variability</emphasis>
. Specimens from Badzhalsky Mt. Range differ from the 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1322,1492,1518]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
population in more lateral position of microsensillum on Abd.III, set very close to the lateral sensillum (like in 
<figureCitation box="[573,664,1572,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="30.[264,382,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[310,1260,721,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-221@30.[286,1294,702,1558]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Scutisotoma longisensilla sp.n. 72, posterior side of manubrium; 73, 74, posterior and anterior sides of dens; 75, Ant.3, lateral view (ls – lateral sensilla); 76–78, variants in position of sensillum and microsensillum on Abd.III (p-chaetae connected by a line, s: sensillum, ms: microsensillum); 79, chaetotaxy of Abd.V (s1–4: accp1–4 sensilla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071492/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). At the moment we regard them as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[264,369,1612,1637]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica">
<emphasis box="[264,369,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1323,1491,1878]" lastBlockId="29.[264,1322,283,430]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,408,1651,1677]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Affinity</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[425,562,1652,1677]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[425,562,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[572,631,1651,1677]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[572,631,1651,1677]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to two new species described below. The first, 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[328,509,1692,1717]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisensilla" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[328,509,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. longisensilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[519,578,1691,1717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[519,578,1691,1717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, has almost the same furcal characters (moderate size, similar chaetotaxy and mucro with 3 teeth), 2 lateral sensilla on Ant.3, and 4+4 tenacular teeth. Differentiating characters are the length of dorsal sensilla (long in 
<emphasis box="[1041,1227,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[1041,1222,1772,1797]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisensilla">S. longisensilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
short in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[264,401,1812,1837]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica">
<emphasis box="[264,401,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), their positions on Abd.V, and the length of the unsetaceous part of anterior side of dens (about 1/2 of dens in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[656,835,1852,1877]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisensilla">
<emphasis box="[656,835,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. longisensilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, about 1/ 
<quantity box="[942,988,1852,1878]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[995,1128,1852,1877]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica">
<emphasis box="[995,1128,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The second, 
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" order="Collembola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schisti" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. schisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[350,409,283,309]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[350,409,283,309]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, can easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[832,970,284,309]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolymica">
<emphasis box="[832,970,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">S. kolymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of only one lateral sensillum on Ant.3 and higher number of chaetae on dens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1322,283,430]" box="[312,1156,363,390]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,472,363,389]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from two localities in the Far East of 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1152,364,390]" name="Russia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[264,1322,283,430]" box="[312,1107,403,430]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,520,403,429]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Name derivation</emphasis>
. The new species is named after the type-locality.
</paragraph>
